'''Ōi Clan''' (大井氏) refers to various Japanese clans: * {{ill|Ki Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, including figures such as {{ill|Ōi Sanespring|ja|大井実春|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Sanespring|qq=}}. * A cadet branch of the {{ill|Shinano Minamoto|ja|信濃源氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Minamoto|qq=}} {{ill|Ogasawara Clan|ja|小笠原氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ogasawara Clan|qq=}}, who also served as deputy governors of {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Province|qq=}}. * A cadet branch of the {{ill|Kai Minamoto|ja|甲斐源氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kai Minamoto|qq=}} {{ill|Takeda Clan|ja|武田氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeda Clan|qq=}}. * A family belonging to the {{ill|Murayama Party|ja|村山党|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murayama Party|qq=}}, one of the {{ill|Seven Parties of Musashi|ja|武蔵七党|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seven Parties of Musashi|qq=}}.
== Ōi Clan (Ki Clan) ==
The branch of the {{ill|Ki Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}} descending from the {{ill|Ki Nagahaseo|ja|紀長谷雄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki Nagahaseo|qq=}} line settled in {{ill|Musashi Province|ja|武蔵国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Musashi Province|qq=}} during the time of {{ill|Ki Saneokina|ja|紀実直|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki Saneokina|qq=}}, associated with provincial government offices. They had deep ties with {{ill|Ise Province|ja|伊勢国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise Province|qq=}}. Apart from the Ōi Clan, their relatives included the {{ill|Shinagawa Clan|ja|品川氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinagawa Clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Kasukabe Clan|ja|春日部氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kasukabe Clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Tsutsumi Clan|ja|堤氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsutsumi Clan|qq=}}, and {{ill|Shioda Clan|ja|潮田氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shioda Clan|qq=}}. It is believed that the Kasukabe Clan served {{ill|Minamoto no Yorimasa|ja|源頼政|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yorimasa|qq=}}.
{{ill|Ōi Sanespring|ja|大井実春|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Sanespring|qq=}} participated in the suppression of the remnants of the {{ill|Taira Clan|ja|平氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira Clan|qq=}} in {{ill|Ise Province|ja|伊勢国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise Province|qq=}}, including {{ill|Shida Yoshihiro|ja|志田義広|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shida Yoshihiro|qq=}}, {{ill|Hirata Ietoki|ja|平田家継|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirata Ietoki|qq=}}, and {{ill|Taira no Nobukane|ja|平信兼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Nobukane|qq=}} in the third year of {{ill|Juei|ja|寿永|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Juei|qq=}} (1184). In {{ill|Gennya|ja|元暦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gennya|qq=}} 2 (1184), he performed ceremonial duties for {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoshitsune|qq=}}. By {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunji|qq=}} 1 (1185), he had been granted fiefs, including the {{ill|Katori District|ja|香取郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katori District|qq=}} in present-day {{ill|Kuwana City|ja|桑名市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuwana City|qq=}}, Mie Prefecture, and later parts of {{ill|Ōi District|ja|大井郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi District|qq=}} and {{ill|Ōmori District|ja|大森郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmori District|qq=}}. The Ōi Clan remained loyal retainers of {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoritomo|qq=}} and were treated favorably. Sanespring was renowned for his strength, participating in sumo matches before Yoritomo.
; References * {{Cite book|author=Ochiai Yoshiaki|title=The Urban Settings and Samurai of the Medieval Eastern Provinces|year=2005|isbn=978-4634523418}} * {{Cite book|author=Noguchi Minoru|title=Eastern Samurai and Kyoto|year=2015|isbn=978-4886217110}}
