The Ōi Clan in {{ill|Kai Province|ja|甲斐国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kai Province|qq=}} centered around {{ill|Ōi Manor|ja|大井荘 (甲斐国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Manor|qq=}}. It served as a cadet branch of the {{ill|Takeda Clan|ja|武田氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeda Clan|qq=}}. During the {{ill|Muromachi Period|ja|室町時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Muromachi Period|qq=}}, they engaged in various battles alongside other regional clans such as the {{ill|Imagawa Clan|ja|今川氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imagawa Clan|qq=}} and {{ill|Murakami Clan|ja|村上氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakami Clan|qq=}}.
Notable figures include: * {{ill|Ōi Nobukiyo|ja|大井信清|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Nobukiyo|qq=}} * {{ill|Ōi Shōji|ja|大井昌次|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Shōji|qq=}}
