The branch of the {{ill|Ki Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}} descending from the [[:en:Ki no Haseo|Ki Nagahaseo]] line settled in [[:en:Musashi Province|Musashi Province]] during the time of {{ill|Ki Saneokina|ja|紀実直|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki Saneokina|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, associated with provincial government offices. They had deep ties with [[:en:Ise Province|Ise Province]]. Apart from the Ōi Clan, their relatives included the {{ill|Shinagawa Clan|ja|品川氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinagawa Clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Kasukabe Clan|ja|春日部氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kasukabe Clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Tsutsumi Clan|ja|堤氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsutsumi Clan|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 若狭島津氏}}, and {{ill|Shioda Clan|ja|潮田氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shioda Clan|qq=}}. It is believed that the Kasukabe Clan served [[:en:Minamoto no Yorimasa|Minamoto no Yorimasa]].
{{ill|Ōi Sanespring|ja|大井実春|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Sanespring|qq=}} participated in the suppression of the remnants of the [[:en:Taira clan|Taira Clan]] in [[:en:Ise Province|Ise Province]], including {{ill|Shida Yoshihiro|ja|志田義広|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shida Yoshihiro|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 源義広 (志田三郎先生)}}, {{ill|Hirata Ietoki|ja|平田家継|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirata Ietoki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 平家継}}, and {{ill|Taira no Nobukane|ja|平信兼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Nobukane|qq=}} in the third year of [[:en:Juei|Juei]] (1184). In [[:en:Genryaku|Gennya]] 2 (1184), he performed ceremonial duties for [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshitsune|Minamoto no Yoshitsune]]. By [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunji]] 1 (1185), he had been granted fiefs, including the [[:en:Katori District|Katori District]] in present-day [[:en:Kuwana, Mie|Kuwana City]], Mie Prefecture, and later parts of {{ill|Ōi District|ja|大井郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi District|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and {{ill|Ōmori District|ja|大森郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmori District|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. The Ōi Clan remained loyal retainers of [[:en:Minamoto no Yoritomo|Minamoto no Yoritomo]] and were treated favorably. Sanespring was renowned for his strength, participating in sumo matches before Yoritomo.
; References * {{Cite book|author=Ochiai Yoshiaki|title=The Urban Settings and Samurai of the Medieval Eastern Provinces|year=2005|isbn=978-4634523418}} * {{Cite book|author=Noguchi Minoru|title=Eastern Samurai and Kyoto|year=2015|isbn=978-4886217110}}
== Ōi Clan (Ogasawara Lineage) ==
The Ōi Clan of Shinano Province originates from [[:en:Ogasawara Nagakiyo|Ogasawara Nagakiyo]]'s seventh son, {{ill|Ōi Tomomitsu|ja|大井朝光|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Tomomitsu|qq=}}, who settled in {{ill|Ōi Manor|ja|大井荘 (信濃国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Manor|qq=}} (present-day [[:en:Saku, Nagano|Saku City]], Nagano Prefecture) following his contributions in the [[:en:Jōkyū War|Jōkyū Rebellion]]. Tomomitsu’s descendants expanded their influence in [[:en:Saku District, Shinano|Saku District]] and allied with prominent clans.
=== Timeline === * [[:en:Kennin|Kengen]] 1 (1275): Financial contributions to {{ill|Wakamiyahachimangu Shrine|ja|若宮八幡宮社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiyahachimangu Shrine|qq=}} were recorded. * [[:en:Kōan (Kamakura period)|Kōan]] 8 (1285): The fall of the [[:en:Tomono clan|Banno Clan]] marked a significant power shift in Saku.
Despite facing challenges during the [[:en:Northern and Southern Courts period (disambiguation)|Nanboku-chō Period]], the Ōi Clan remained influential, continuing to expand under the governance of the [[:en:Ashikaga clan|Ashikaga Clan]]. However, their power waned after the defeat during the {{ill|Ōtō Conflict|ja|大塔合戦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtō Conflict|qq=}}.
=== Genealogy === {{familytree/start}} {{familytree|n1=Ogasawara Nagakiyo|n2=Tomomitsu}} {{familytree/end}}
== Ōi Clan (Takeda Lineage) ==
The Ōi Clan in [[:en:Kai Province|Kai Province]] centered around {{ill|Ōi Manor|ja|大井荘 (甲斐国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Manor|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. It served as a cadet branch of the [[:en:Takeda clan|Takeda Clan]]. During the [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi Period]], they engaged in various battles alongside other regional clans such as the [[:en:Imagawa clan|Imagawa Clan]] and {{ill|Murakami Clan|ja|村上氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakami Clan|qq=}}.
Notable figures include: * {{ill|Ōi Nobukiyo|ja|大井信清|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Nobukiyo|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} * {{ill|Ōi Shōji|ja|大井昌次|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Shōji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
